  "text": "Notably, an intraperitoneal injection of lipopolysaccharide (LPS), an inflammation inducing endotoxin, was found to result in memory impairments in mice [CITATION_1] . In addition, repeated injections of LPS enhanced b-amyloid generation, and conversely, treatment with anti-inflammatory agents suppressed LPS-induced amyloidogenesis, memory dysfunction, and neuronal cell death [CITATION_2] . In this study, it was also found that inflammation resulted in an accumulation of b-amyloid 1-42 via increased b-and csecretase activities accompanied by elevated APP expression and astrocyte activation [CITATION_3] .",
